#: ../../../reference/generated/numpy.choose.rst:4
msgid "numpy.choose"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:2
msgid ""
"Construct an array from an index array and a list of arrays to choose from."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:4
msgid ""
"First of all, if confused or uncertain, definitely look at the Examples - in "
"its full generality, this function is less simple than it might seem from "
"the following code description::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:8
msgid "np.choose(a,c) == np.array([c[a[I]][I] for I in np.ndindex(a.shape)])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:10
msgid "But this omits some subtleties.  Here is a fully general summary:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:12
msgid ""
"Given an \"index\" array (`a`) of integers and a sequence of ``n`` arrays "
"(`choices`), `a` and each choice array are first broadcast, as necessary, to "
"arrays of a common shape; calling these *Ba* and *Bchoices[i], i = 0,...,"
"n-1* we have that, necessarily, ``Ba.shape == Bchoices[i].shape`` for each "
"``i``.  Then, a new array with shape ``Ba.shape`` is created as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:19
msgid ""
"if ``mode='raise'`` (the default), then, first of all, each element of ``a`` "
"(and thus ``Ba``) must be in the range ``[0, n-1]``; now, suppose that ``i`` "
"(in that range) is the value at the ``(j0, j1, ..., jm)`` position in ``Ba`` "
"- then the value at the same position in the new array is the value in "
"``Bchoices[i]`` at that same position;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:25
msgid ""
"if ``mode='wrap'``, values in `a` (and thus `Ba`) may be any (signed) "
"integer; modular arithmetic is used to map integers outside the range `[0, "
"n-1]` back into that range; and then the new array is constructed as above;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:30
msgid ""
"if ``mode='clip'``, values in `a` (and thus ``Ba``) may be any (signed) "
"integer; negative integers are mapped to 0; values greater than ``n-1`` are "
"mapped to ``n-1``; and then the new array is constructed as above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:39
msgid "**a**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:-1
msgid "int array"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:37
msgid ""
"This array must contain integers in ``[0, n-1]``, where ``n`` is the number "
"of choices, unless ``mode=wrap`` or ``mode=clip``, in which cases any "
"integers are permissible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:45
msgid "**choices**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:-1
msgid "sequence of arrays"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:42
msgid ""
"Choice arrays. `a` and all of the choices must be broadcastable to the same "
"shape.  If `choices` is itself an array (not recommended), then its "
"outermost dimension (i.e., the one corresponding to ``choices.shape[0]``) is "
"taken as defining the \"sequence\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:50
msgid "**out**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:-1
msgid "array, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:48
msgid ""
"If provided, the result will be inserted into this array. It should be of "
"the appropriate shape and dtype. Note that `out` is always buffered if "
"``mode='raise'``; use other modes for better performance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:57
msgid "**mode**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:-1
msgid "{'raise' (default), 'wrap', 'clip'}, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:53
msgid "Specifies how indices outside ``[0, n-1]`` will be treated:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:55
msgid "'raise' : an exception is raised"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:56
msgid "'wrap' : value becomes value mod ``n``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:57
msgid "'clip' : values < 0 are mapped to 0, values > n-1 are mapped to n-1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:65
msgid "**merged_array**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:-1
msgid "array"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.choose:62
msgid "The merged result."
msgstr ""

